<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN BUTTERFLY PHOTOGRAPHER TO EXHIBIT IN NEW YORK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York, May 16 (CNA) 05/16/07  19:48:21 (By Lilian Lin and Ruth
Wang)
</P>
<P>
Taiwanese butterfly photographer Tsai Bae-chun will showcase his
photo collection of Taiwan's endemic butterflies at the Cultural
Center of the Taipei Economic and Cultural Office in New York
from May 17-18, Shao Ping-yun, the office's press division chief,
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tsai was invited to exhibit his photos at the Smithsonian Museum
of Natural History in Washington D. C. in early May and received
a lot of praise, Shao said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will display more than 40 shots of Taiwan's
butterflies  that Tsai spent  nearly  30 years  tracking  and
photographing.
</P>
<P>
Stories of the talented butterfly photographer, who won the
National Literature and Art Achievement Award and has published
many books on Taiwan's butterflies, have been included in
elementary school textbooks, Shao said, adding that he hopes the
New York exhibition will prompt more people to cherish nature.
</P>
